{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now a certain man was sick, named Lazarus, of Bethany, the town of Mary and her sister Martha."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It was that Mary which anointed the Lord with ointment, and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Therefore his sisters sent unto him, saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, behold, he whom thou lovest is sick.",
          "speaker": "Mary and Martha"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When Jesus heard that, he said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When he had heard therefore that he was sick, he abode two days still in the same place where he was."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then after that saith he to his disciples,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Master, the Jews of late sought to stone thee; and goest thou thither again?",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jesus answered,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These things said he: and after that he saith unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, if he sleep, he shall do well.",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Howbeit Jesus spake of his death: but they thought that he had spoken of taking of rest in sleep."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then said Jesus unto them plainly,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Let us also go, that we may die with him.",
          "speaker": "Thomas"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, if thou hadst been here, my brother had not died.",
          "speaker": "Martha"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "But I know, that even now, whatsoever thou wilt ask of God, God will give it thee.",
          "speaker": "Martha"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jesus saith unto her,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I know that he shall rise again in the resurrection at the last day.",
          "speaker": "Martha"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jesus said unto her,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Yea, Lord: I believe that thou art the Christ, the Son of God, which should come into the world.",
          "speaker": "Martha"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 47,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then gathered the chief priests and the Pharisees a council, and said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "What do we? for this man doeth many miracles.",
          "speaker": "Chief Priests and Pharisees"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Plot to Kill Jesus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 55,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the Jews' passover was nigh at hand: and many went out of the country up to Jerusalem before the passover, to purify themselves."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Preparation for Passover"
      ]
    }
  ]
}